> 
> If the product description says 'SI1-SI2,' you must assume the majority of the stones are SI2. In 2026, I am seeing more 'rejected' industrial-grade diamonds being funneled into natural tennis bracelets to keep prices competitive against lab-grown.  
>   
> If you want a bracelet that truly dances in the light, you either need to pay for a **VS-clarity upgrade** or move to **[Lab-Grown](https://diamondcritics.com/lab-grown-vs-natural-diamond-price/)** where VS quality is the standard.
