### The Clasp Audit: Your Insurance Policy

The clasp is the only thing standing between your wrist and a lost diamond. On Blue Nile, you will see several types of closures depending on the "Extraordinary Collection" or standard tiers.

-   **The Double-Safety Catch:** This features a primary box clasp and two "wings" on the side that snap shut. This is the **GIA Expert standard**.  
    
-   **The Flower Clasp (New for 2026):** Featured on the **[James Allen for Blue Nile](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/by-james-allen?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews)** line, this uses a decorative but secure mechanism.  
    
-   **The Hidden Box Clasp:** Seamless but riskier; if the internal tongue loses its "spring," the bracelet can slide off unnoticed.

