olite-bracelet-in-14k-rose-gold-item-149101?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blue_nile_reviews" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">$2,470</a></strong></td><td><strong>Extreme</strong></td><td>Unbeatable "statement" color for the price.</td></tr></tbody></table>

### The "High-End" Arbitrage: The Sapphire Hack

If you are moving into the **$5,000+ bracket**, Blue Nile’s **Extraordinary Collection** of gemstones offers a way to bypass the high cost of natural diamonds while maintaining a "Diamond Look" through alternating settings.

-   **The Sapphire Power Play:** In our 2026 audit, we tracked a stunning **[Oval Sapphire and Diamond Semi-Bezel-Set Bracelet (18k White Gold)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/bracelets/oval-sapphire-and-diamond-semi-bezel-set-bracelet-in-18k-white-gold-5x4mm-item-194500?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews)**. The original price of **$11,670** dropped to **$8,169** during the Spring Sale.  
    
-   **The Comparison:** For the same **$8,169**, you could only afford a **4-carat natural diamond bracelet** with lower H-I/SI2 clarity. By choosing the Sapphire alternative, you get a higher gold karat (18K vs 14K) and a significantly more expensive "Designer" look.

