## Point #5: Sizing and The Return Policy

A poorly weighted or incorrectly sized tennis bracelet will "flip" upside down on your wrist, hiding the diamonds and exposing the metal base. Standard bracelet length is **7 inches**, but Blue Nile offers **7.5" and 8"** options for larger wrists.

While Blue Nile’s 4-prong settings are well-weighted to stay upright, if the fit is too loose, gravity will inevitably cause the bracelet to flip.

### The Physics of the "Flip": Sizing Data

On Blue Nile, the most common reason for "The Flip" is buying a standard 7-inch length for a 6-inch wrist. A tennis bracelet should have just enough room to slide one finger between the chain and your skin.

Any more, and the "top-heavy" nature of the diamonds will rotate them toward the floor.

